      How many players are there in hockey?
      11 players
      How many players in hockey? In hockey, each team has 11 players, including 10 field players and one goalkeeper. There are five substitutes on the bench and there is no limit to the number of times a player is allowed to be substituted. This is commonly known as rolling substitution.May 3, 2022

      Are there 11 players in hockey?
      There are 11 players on a team made up of a goalkeeper, defenders, midfielders and forwards. The only player on the field who is allowed to use their feet and hands as well as their stick is the goalkeeper.
